tools where it looks

00:14:07.740 --> 00:14:10.050
sort of like a little
roller, and those are fine.

00:14:10.050 --> 00:14:14.190
But I think if you go to get
professional microneedling,

00:14:14.190 --> 00:14:17.140
I highly, highly believe
in it, where again,

00:14:17.140 --> 00:14:19.500
it's sort of this merger
of technology and skin care

00:14:19.500 --> 00:14:22.710
and everything else where the
thought process behind it is

00:14:22.710 --> 00:14:25.770
basically-- if you've ever had a
laser treatment, it's similar--

00:14:25.770 --> 00:14:28.290
that if you get a
little cut on your skin,

00:14:28.290 --> 00:14:32.172
our skin is miraculous
because it can heal itself.

00:14:32.172 --> 00:14:33.630
So it's sort of a
similar situation

00:14:33.630 --> 00:14:35.713
of where it's creating
these little micro-injuries

00:14:35.713 --> 00:14:37.540
in your skin that
then heal themselves,

00:14:37.540 --> 00:14:41.070
and then they're producing
more collagen. That one, I

00:14:41.070 --> 00:14:43.280
truly, truly believe in.

00:14:43.280 --> 00:14:45.030
