I don't know.

00:50:18.700 --> 00:50:19.200
[CHUCKLING]

00:50:19.200 --> 00:50:20.820
AUDIENCE: Uh-huh.

00:50:20.820 --> 00:50:23.580
MICHELLE LEE: Our services are
not necessarily mental health.

00:50:23.580 --> 00:50:27.940
But for our staff, we have a
lot of beauty services, frankly.

00:50:27.940 --> 00:50:30.918
We've got like a brow
person who comes in.

00:50:30.918 --> 00:50:31.710
It's more sort of--

00:50:31.710 --> 00:50:33.210
AUDIENCE: Well,
that's more external

00:50:33.210 --> 00:50:36.630
and that, you know, that, I
mean, not that it's not good,

00:50:36.630 --> 00:50:41.460
but that there's also a need for
women to be internally happy.

00:50:41.460 --> 00:50:44.040
And folks who come from
different backgrounds, folks

00:50:44.040 --> 00:50:48.048
of color often have some
internal unbeautiful feelings.

00:50:48.048 --> 00:50:48.840
MICHELLE LEE: Yeah.

00:50:48.840 --> 00:50:49.340
So--

00:50:49.340 --> 00:50:52.500
AUDIENCE: And so I just wonder,
I've got to-- that's what I do.

00:50:52.500 --> 00:50:55.410
So I always wonder about
the internal beauty.

00:50:55.410 --> 00:51:00.060
And when we look at things
in women, like, you know,

00:51:00.060 --> 00:51:03.210
I can see the beauty that
comes from external, both bath

00:51:03.210 --> 00:51:04.630
gel, brows, makeup.

00:51:04.630 --> 00:51:08.220
But when they sit before
me, they're cutting,

00:51:08.220 --> 00:51:10.350
they're not eating,
they're drinking too much.

00:51:10.350 --> 00:51:13.680
And they can be very successful
in any place in their life.

00:51:13.680 --> 00:51:16.920
But they're really damaging
themselves or damaging families

00:51:16.920 --> 00:51:19.437
by lack of emotional
intelligence.

00:51:19.437 --> 00:51:20.770
And then they don't make great--

00:51:20.770 --> 00:51:22.290
they're not a great
team member when

00:51:22.290 --> 00:51:23.520
they're before you
because they're

00:51:23.520 --> 00:51:24.660
doing all this other stuff.

00:51:24.660 --> 00:51:27.450
They've got great
brows, and that's good.

00:51:27.450 --> 00:51:30.330
But there's some-- so
I'm just wondering.

00:51:30.330 --> 00:51:30.830
Is there--

00:51:30.830 --> 00:51:31.590
MICHELLE LEE: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:51:31.590 --> 00:51:33.257
So at our larger
company, actually, this

00:51:33.257 --> 00:51:35.040
is a somewhat newer
thing this past year.

00:51:35.040 --> 00:51:37.720
So we've actually launched
a bunch of groups.

00:51:37.720 --> 00:51:41.130
One has been a Latinx group.

00:51:41.130 --> 00:51:43.890
One is a women's network,
which just launched probably

00:51:43.890 --> 00:51:44.850
about six months ago.

00:51:44.850 --> 00:51:47.670
And I'm actually the executive
sponsor of the women's network.

00:51:47.670 --> 00:51:50.522
So within a lot of these smaller
groups within Condé Nast,

00:51:50.522 --> 00:51:52.980
these are actually some of
those things that are happening.

00:51:52.980 --> 00:51:54.270
We'll do other events.

00:51:54.270 --> 00:51:57.150
There's smaller
mentorship programs,

00:51:57.150 --> 00:51:59.340
not necessarily always
